.env variables are in .env.local
Make things simple, dont overcomplicate things.
Reuse existing components if possible.
Make sure each logicand functionality is Rock Solid!
If some function or logic is too long or complicated, split into smaller mini functions to make sure it is easy to manage.

## IF changing UI/UX REQUIREMENTS
- **Responsive**: Mobile-first with Tailwind breakpoints
- **Modern**: smooth animations, premium feel
- **Navigation**: No dead ends, always provide back/home options
- **States**: Loading, error, and empty states for all data
- **Keep components SMALL**: Max 30 lines per component
- **Break down large UI**: If component exceeds 30 lines, split into smaller sub-components within same file
- **Always close JSX tags**: Verify every <div>, <span>, etc. has proper closing tag
- **One responsibility**: Each component should do ONE thing only
- **Import React**: Always include import React from 'react' in JSX files


# VibeKit App Structure Guide

## 🏗️ Architecture Overview
**Next.js 15 + Clerk Auth + Convex DB + Stripe + Tailwind CSS**

## 📁 Core Structure

### `/docs/app/` - Main Application
```
app/
├── (app)/                    # Protected app routes
│   ├── page.tsx             # Home/Projects page
│   ├── client-page.tsx      # Projects list client component
│   ├── profile/             # User profile page
│   ├── billing/             # Stripe billing page  
│   ├── settings/            # Settings page
│   └── projects/[id]/       # Project details
│       └── [agentId]/       # Agent configuration
├── (auth)/                  # Auth routes (sign-in/up)
├── (embed)/                 # Embeddable widget routes
├── api/                     # API routes
├── layout.tsx               # Root layout with providers
└── globals.css              # Global styles
```

## 🔧 Key Components & Patterns

### **Page Pattern**
```typescript
// Server component (page.tsx)
export default async function Page() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  return <ClientPage userId={userId} />;
}

// Client component (client-page.tsx)
"use client";
export default function ClientPage() {
  const { sidebarOpen } = useSidebar();
  return (
    <div className={cn("flex-1 transition-all", 
      sidebarOpen ? "ml-42" : "ml-14.5")}>
      {/* Page content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### **Core Files**
- `config.ts` - Site config & navigation
- `middleware.ts` - Route protection
- `components/navbar.tsx` - Sidebar navigation
- `components/conditional-layout.tsx` - Layout wrapper

## 🗄️ Database (Convex)
```typescript
// Main entities
- organization (Stripe integration)
- userProfile (user settings)
- project (user projects)
- agent (AI agent configs)
- actionLog (activity tracking)
```

## 🔐 Auth & Protection
- **Clerk** for authentication
- **Middleware** protects `/(projects|profile|billing|settings)(.*)`
- **Conditional Layout** shows navbar for signed-in users

## 🎨 UI System
- **Tailwind CSS** + **shadcn/ui** components
- **Responsive**: `sidebarOpen ? "ml-42" : "ml-14.5"` pattern
- **Icons**: SVG files in `/public/`
- **Forms**: `react-hook-form` + `zod` validation

## 📊 State Management
- **Convex** for server state
- **React Context** for sidebar state
- **Clerk** for user state

## 🚀 Key Features
- Project management with AI agents
- Stripe billing integration  
- GitHub OAuth integration
- Real-time updates via Convex
- Embeddable widgets
- Activity logging

## 🛠️ Development Commands
```bash
npm run dev        # Development server
npm run build      # Production build  
npm run lint       # ESLint checking
```

This structure follows **mobile-first responsive design** with **component composition** and **server/client separation** patterns.